## Project Structure

```
├── src/
│   └── valet_parking/
│       ├── __init__.py          # Package initialization
│       ├── exceptions.py         # Custom exceptions
│       ├── config.py            # Configuration settings
│       ├── core/                # Core business logic
│       │   ├── qr_generator.py  # QR code generation
│       │   ├── time_calculator.py # Time and fee calculations
│       │   └── reservation_service.py # Main service
│       ├── models/              # Data models
│       │   └── reservation.py   # Customer, Vehicle, Reservation
│       ├── storage/             # Data persistence
│       │   ├── repository.py    # Repository interface
│       │   └── in_memory_repository.py # In-memory implementation
│       └── utils/               # Utility functions
│           ├── validators.py    # Input validation
│           └── formatters.py    # Output formatting
├── tests/
│   ├── conftest.py             # Shared test fixtures
│   ├── unit/                   # Unit tests
│   └── integration/            # Integration tests
├── plan/                       # Planning documents
│   └── out_doc/                # Generated plans and specs
├── pyproject.toml              # Project metadata and dependencies
└── README.md                   # This file
```

## Architecture

The system follows clean architecture principles with clear separation of concerns:

- **Models Layer**: Pydantic models for data validation and serialization
- **Core Layer**: Business logic for reservations, QR codes, and time calculation
- **Storage Layer**: Repository pattern for data persistence (currently in-memory, extendable to databases)
- **Utils Layer**: Reusable validation and formatting utilities

## Testing

The project maintains high test coverage (80%+) with comprehensive unit and integration tests:

- **Unit Tests**: Test individual components in isolation
- **Integration Tests**: Test complete workflows end-to-end
- **Test Fixtures**: Shared fixtures in `conftest.py` for consistency

